You are having difficulty with shared libraries on the system. Which of the following com-mands will print the current directories and libraries in the cache?
A)  ldconfig - C
B)  ldd - f
C)  ldconfig - p
D)  ldd - b
C
C. The ldconfig command is used to work with the library cache, and the - p optionprints the directories and libraries in the cache. The - C option informs ldconfig to use adifferent cache. The ldd command prints the library dependencies for a given command, butthe options given dont exist for ldd.
